  24 Mar 2005; Gregorio Guidi <greg_g@gentoo.org> kig-3.4.0.ebuild:
  Use local flag 'kig-scripting' instead of 'python' to enable scripting
  support, disabling it by default (#85925).

  18 Mar 2005; Daniel Goller <morfic@gentoo.org> kig-3.4.0.ebuild:
  Added to ~ppc

  13 Mar 2005; Dan Armak <danarmak@gentoo.org> kig-3.4.0.ebuild:
  KDE 3.4.0 ebuilds. Note that the tarballs won't be officially released for a
  few more days.

  13 Mar 2005; Marcus D. Hanwell <cryos@gentoo.org> kig-3.4.0_rc1.ebuild:
  Marked ~amd64, keywording KDE split ebuilds, bug 80944.

*kig-3.4.0_rc1 (28 Feb 2005)

  28 Feb 2005; Gregorio Guidi <greg_g@gentoo.org> kig-3.4.0_rc1.ebuild:
  Add optional support for python scripting.

  27 Feb 2005; Dan Armak <danarmak@gentoo.org> :
  Ebuild for 3.4.0 RC1.

*kig-3.4.0_beta2 (05 Feb 2005)

  05 Feb 2005; Dan Armak <danarmak@gentoo.org> +kig-3.4.0_beta2.ebuild:
  Ebuild for 3.4.0_beta2. Note that beta2 has NOT been released as of this
  date. This ebuild is for inside testing by the KDE team, and is of course
  package.masked.

*kig-3.4.0_beta1 (15 Jan 2005)

  15 Jan 2005; Dan Armak <danarmak@gentoo.org> +metadata.xml,
  +kig-3.4.0_beta1.ebuild:
  Adding the split ebuilds to portage. For KDE 3.4, we've created separate
  ebuilds for all the KDE apps.

